Click on the video and watch the entire video in 480 or higher quality. If you have a poor connection, do not change the quality at all. 5. Watch 3 or 4 related videos (10 minutes). 6.  Repeat from step 3 DONâ€™T :  1. Do not repeat playing the video without watching other videos. 2. Do not watch the video in incognito mode. 3. Do not delete the search history. 4. Continue to str**m even if the views freeze, your views still count. 5. Stay away from spam comments (write the comment over and over). 6. Do not use emoji. 7. Fantasy please read this! I know as a fandom there are many things we need to improve, but please stop saying strong words like "it's a very lazy fandom", "I hate this fandom" and so on...it's not nice to read that kind of comments. These days on fantasy twitter have not been the best for some because of this kind of comments and other major problems. I know some people said it to get Fantasy to react and support SF9 but it still wasn't the way.  Some criticized our fanbases saying that the goals they set were unrealistic and blaming them, when none of those people thought that this goal could have been set because in the Good Guy and Summer Breeze era they did set ads, despite that we have to value the effort of all our fanbases since they dedicate part of their time in informing us about voting, making tutorials for the apps and more things to support SF9. Although it is seen that there is little participation from Fantasy, as for example there is currently a vote for an ad for the anniversary of SF9 in the THEKKING app, there are less than 10 days to close that vote and we are not even half way to the goal :(.  I know that apart from SF9 we all have a life, but if you have some free time, collect votes in all the apps, even if what you contribute is little it doesn't matter, it is very useful even if you don't believe it. To know in which apps you have to collect votes and more information about SF9, I recommend you follow this twitter account: @/SupernovaLatam Also we should improve in str3am, if you can str3am all SF9 mvs but if you don't have enough time give priority to Tear Drop and Summer Breeze. And let's support SF9 by watching all their content: like their covers (recently Inseong did a cover, it's been a week and still hasn't reached 100k v1ews), the shows they participated/participated in or listening to the members' soundcloud. They did several things for us but they don't have enough support :(  I hope we improve as a fandom and show more support for the guys, and treat each other with respect. Remember we are like family to them, SF9 have Fantasy and Fantasy has SF9.   I just wanted to say all this, take care of yourselves and I hope you have a great day!
A. M. A. Z. I. N. G.

The right way for STR**MING : 1. Open YouTube from any browser or use the YouTube app. 2.  Log in to your account. 3.  Search for the SF9 performance through the search field. 4.  Click on the video and watch the entire video in 480 or higher quality. If you have a poor connection, do not change the quality at all. 5. Watch 3 or 4 related videos (10 minutes). 6.  Repeat from step 3 DONâ€™T :  1. Do not repeat playing the video without watching other videos. 2. Do not watch the video in incognito mode. 3. Do not delete the search history. 4. Continue to str**m even if the views freeze, your views still count. 5. Stay away from spam comments (write the comment over and over). 6. Do not use emoji. 7. Do not use playlist in first 24 hours. 8. Do not mute the sound, use headphones. 9. From time to time watch the video through an embedded video in an article, make sure you are logged in. 10. During the first 24 hours, refrain from pausing the video, moving it forward, or replaying a part.  11. The chance to delete views is less when you subscribe to the YouTube service ( youtube premium ). 12. NEVER use playlist.

Hello fantasy! (Beware, this is a long post) I'm a new Fantasy. I discovered them a month ago  (i pity myself that i just knew them now). Anyway, what I wanted to say is that, these MEN (not boys) deserves to be on top. They deserve more recognition. They are fantastic and their songs are all bop. I mean, just listen to Tear Drop. It is different from all the mainstream kpop songs out now.  Before being a fantasy, i am a hardcore VIP (until now). It is really hard for me to stan other artist even from the same company. But when i discover SF9, the game changes. Its like a 360 turn for me. And now i'm like, what the hell i've been doing for the past 4 years? SF9 are talented af.   They are unique, (been listening to their discography everyday and they are all lit)  the funniest (their brotherhood and bromances are just amazing), talented musicians and artists (composer and choreographer in the group? They got'em) and most importantly, they love their fans so much. Not saying that the other groups didnt. But the more I got to know them, the more I discover how much the Fantasy means to them. They are so full of gratitude. And I love it. Goes to show that they are passionate to what they are doing.   My only regret is discovering them late. But still, better late than never, right? So yeah, stan SF9 for a better life.   If you read it up to this end, thank you. Told you it will be long.

YouTubeÂ wants to make sure that video views are coming from real people. Thatâ€™s why a YouTube view is only counted when the following two criteria apply: A userÂ intentionallyÂ initiates the watching of a video. The user watches it on the platform forÂ at least 30 seconds. If you skip through a video but theÂ total timeÂ you spend watching isÂ more than 30 seconds, the view will count too. If you watch for less than 30 seconds, it probablyÂ wonâ€™t. Other reasons for YouTube not counting views are: YouTubeÂ wonâ€™t countÂ a watchÂ from aÂ user who leavesÂ spam commentsÂ on videos. YouTube willÂ notÂ count the views of videos that areÂ embedded in a page andÂ autostart.

The right way for STR**MING : 1. Open YouTube from any browser or use the YouTube app. 2.  Log in to your account. 3.  Search for the SF9 performance through the search field. 4.  Click on the video and watch the entire video in 480 or higher quality. If you have a poor connection, do not change the quality at all. 5. Watch 3 or 4 related videos (10 minutes). 6.  Repeat from step 3 DONâ€™T :  1. Do not repeat playing the video without watching other videos. 2. Do not watch the video in incognito mode. 3. Do not delete the search history. 4. Continue to str**m even if the views freeze, your views still count. 5. Stay away from spam comments (write the comment over and over). 6. Do not use emoji. 7. Do not use playlist in first 24 hours. 8. Do not mute the sound, use headphones. 9. From time to time watch the video through an embedded video in an article, make sure you are logged in. 10. During the first 24 hours, refrain from pausing the video, moving it forward, or replaying a part.  11. The chance to delete views is less when you subscribe to the YouTube service ( youtube premium ). 12. NEVER use playlist.

Guys don't you think this song is made so clever? (This comment is long so please read it if you have enough time:)   â–ªThe setting (held in aesthatic tones and elements, very pleasing for our eyes, no colorful and exaggerated things like the whole CGI things kpop mostly has in the M/Vs). There are so many details, but it is not confusing. I really like the beginning of the m/v. I felt like I'm in an art gallery and since I like art it was just the perfect beginning for me.   The members are portrayed like sculptures and only the one singing moves. I think this is a great detail. For example Zuho who just said "yeah" at the beginning. It was literally just one second but he got the attention. It was perfectly set and my eyes immediately went to him and then back to Dawon. And then the camera moving to Youngbin. "Let's figure it out", this is a perfect detail to the song because there you can see the contrast between Dawon's and Youngbin's voices and that they fit perfectly together.   And then the set was changed and now it is Inseong's time to shine. First the focus was on the table with the glasses to introduce the set and then we can see Inseong singing. This part is very beautiful because his voice is really strong and his vocals are very defined. This has given the song stability and power. The beginning was very calming and now Inseong has given the pain that you have after a while being apart from the person you love altough he/she just sits infront of you. His voice really fits that emotion and has brought the song to a whole new level.   Then following with Taeyang's part it has gotten a bit calmer again. This is a perfect balance because for me it represents that love sickness can be louder (like in Inseong's part) and then it calms down. Taeyang sitting on this chair and the cameraÂ  ankle and position is very good and has given a whole new atmosphere to the m/v. Then the camera moves to his face and the new set is shown. And then he is falling and we go to the next place.  EDIT: please click the "answering button" to continue reading..
